  A man identified as Chukwuma Anthony Ezeh, slumped and died at the arrival hall of the Murtala Mohammed International Airport in Lagos on Wednesday. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that the man was returning from China aboard an Ethiopian Airline flight. “While walking at the arrival hall, the man slumped and died,” spokesperson for the MMIA Police Command, Joseph Alabi said. He noted that the corpse had been deposited at the Air Force Base Hospital mortuary. Alabi said the patient was rushed to the MMIA clinic on Wednesday afternoon but was pronounced dead on arrival. 